1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,640
"Danny's Restaurant"

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:04,940
Don't be ridiculous!

3
00:00:04,940 --> 00:00:08,040
"Akira Hashizume (38)" -Why do I have to apologize?

4
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:11,640
"Hiroshi Kagazume (38)" -Don't play dumb! You know exactly why!

5
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:16,240
I was just doing my job! Don't act so self-righteous!

6
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:18,340
You arrogant jerk!

7
00:00:18,340 --> 00:00:20,740
-What was that? -What?

8
00:00:20,740 --> 00:00:26,140
Excuse me, but could you keep your voices down,

9
00:00:26,140 --> 00:00:28,840
Mr. Hashizume and Mr. Kagazume?

10
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:31,040
-I'm Kagazume! -I'm Hashizume!

11
00:00:32,940 --> 00:00:37,040
-I'm terribly sorry! -They're at it again.

12
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:40,740
"Kimiko Kuwana (36)" -I wish they'd stop. I'm sick of it.

13
00:00:40,740 --> 00:00:43,440
"Shingo Hosoda (28)" -It started a year ago.

14
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:46,140
They're making it hard for me to do my job.

15
00:00:46,140 --> 00:00:47,840
What a nuisance.

16
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:52,940
It was their fault it nearly turned into a murder.

17
00:00:56,940 --> 00:00:59,040
When the countdown reaches zero,

18
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:01,540
use your detective skills to produce an answer!

19
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:05,840
They're so alike, but they get along terribly!

20
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,840
Their case is full of complex mysteries!

21
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,340
He sees through the one and only truth.

22
00:01:09,340 --> 00:01:11,140
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

23
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:13,440
His name is Detective Conan!

24
00:02:58,181 --> 00:03:03,981
"Birds of a Feather at Loggerheads"

25
00:03:08,081 --> 00:03:10,481
Those guys sure are weird.

26
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:11,681
Huh?

27
00:03:11,681 --> 00:03:13,981
They seem to hate each other,

28
00:03:13,981 --> 00:03:16,781
-but they're identical in every way. -You sure?

29
00:03:16,781 --> 00:03:17,981
Shut up already!

30
00:03:17,981 --> 00:03:20,181
You're right. Even their names...

31
00:03:20,181 --> 00:03:22,981
Hashizume and Kagazume.

32
00:03:22,981 --> 00:03:24,481
Tsume and Tsume.

33
00:03:24,481 --> 00:03:26,481
Maybe they don't like that.

34
00:03:26,481 --> 00:03:31,581
Well, birds of a feather either love or hate each other.

35
00:03:31,581 --> 00:03:33,881
This is the last time! You'd better not regret it!

36
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:35,881
Enough already, you hypocrite!

37
00:03:41,381 --> 00:03:42,481
Huh?

38
00:03:46,981 --> 00:03:48,581
Hey.

39
00:03:48,581 --> 00:03:51,881
This is his, right?

40
00:03:51,881 --> 00:03:54,781
-Thank you. -Didn't he take the wrong one?

41
00:03:54,781 --> 00:03:57,181
Yeah...

42
00:03:57,181 --> 00:03:59,781
I'll switch with him later.

43
00:04:08,281 --> 00:04:09,281
"Mouri Detective Agency"

44
00:04:09,281 --> 00:04:10,381
I see.

45
00:04:10,381 --> 00:04:12,781
"Nichiuri Sports - News Archive" -So this is the case

46
00:04:12,781 --> 00:04:14,581
"Major company executive is dead!" -they were referring to.

47
00:04:14,581 --> 00:04:18,781
Yeah. After the president of a major company died,

48
00:04:18,781 --> 00:04:20,881
his will disappeared.

49
00:04:20,881 --> 00:04:22,181
I remember now.

50
00:04:22,181 --> 00:04:25,781
Weekly magazines were full of stories about the family

51
00:04:25,781 --> 00:04:28,281
accusing each other of stealing it.

52
00:04:28,281 --> 00:04:30,581
That was these two.

53
00:04:30,581 --> 00:04:32,181
"Hiroshi Kagazume" -Two Nichiuri Sports reporters

54
00:04:32,181 --> 00:04:34,481
"Akira Hashizume" -famous for their articles on scandals.

55
00:04:34,481 --> 00:04:36,681
They even made comments on TV.

56
00:04:36,681 --> 00:04:38,581
And exacerbated the situation.

57
00:04:38,581 --> 00:04:42,381
They even wrote scandalous articles about the arguing family members.

58
00:04:42,381 --> 00:04:44,781
Ultimately, the family members clashed,

59
00:04:44,781 --> 00:04:46,981
resulting in an attempted murder.

60
00:04:46,981 --> 00:04:51,581
I heard they garnered a lot of criticism and magazine sales fell.

61
00:04:51,581 --> 00:04:55,581
And they're still suffering the consequences.

62
00:04:55,581 --> 00:04:57,281
And that...

63
00:05:00,381 --> 00:05:03,081
turned out the worst way possible.

64
00:05:07,581 --> 00:05:09,381
We've identified the victim.

65
00:05:09,381 --> 00:05:12,581
"Nichiuri Sports Newspaper Company" -Hiroshi Kagazume, 38 years old.

66
00:05:12,581 --> 00:05:15,481
He was a reporter for Nichiuri Sports magazine.

67
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:19,981
The time of death is between 7 pm and 9 pm.

68
00:05:19,981 --> 00:05:21,181
How did he die?

69
00:05:21,181 --> 00:05:23,581
We're still waiting for the autopsy,

70
00:05:23,581 --> 00:05:24,781
but judging by the body's condition,

71
00:05:24,781 --> 00:05:28,581
we believe it was cyanide poisoning.

72
00:05:28,581 --> 00:05:32,881
It's likely it was dissolved into the coffee in his travel tumbler.

73
00:05:32,881 --> 00:05:34,381
Was it suicide?

74
00:05:34,381 --> 00:05:37,981
That's what we thought at first, but...

75
00:05:37,981 --> 00:05:39,881
Footprints?

76
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:43,881
Yes. They're not the victim's and they're fairly fresh.

77
00:05:43,881 --> 00:05:44,881
In other words,

78
00:05:44,881 --> 00:05:49,581
it's possible someone else was here around the time of death.

79
00:05:55,781 --> 00:05:58,081
Akira Hashizume.

80
00:05:58,081 --> 00:06:01,681
Like the late Hiroshi Kagazume,

81
00:06:01,681 --> 00:06:03,881
you're a reporter at Nichiuri Sports, correct?

82
00:06:03,881 --> 00:06:08,581
Yeah. Anyway, why am I being arrested?

83
00:06:08,581 --> 00:06:10,481
You're not under arrest.

84
00:06:10,481 --> 00:06:15,581
We just want to speak with you as a material witness for now.

85
00:06:18,281 --> 00:06:20,581
Kagazume and I got along like cats and dogs.

86
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:23,881
We always fought. It was a huge nuisance.

87
00:06:23,881 --> 00:06:28,581
I'm sure my coworkers have already told you that.

88
00:06:28,581 --> 00:06:32,781
So I definitely had a motive to kill him.

89
00:06:32,781 --> 00:06:36,681
But you didn't?

90
00:06:36,681 --> 00:06:38,581
Of course not!

91
00:06:38,581 --> 00:06:40,181
Then why were your fingerprints found

92
00:06:40,181 --> 00:06:43,181
"Travel Tumbler Fingerprint Results" -on the travel tumbler.

93
00:06:43,181 --> 00:06:45,981
"Name: Akira Hashizume" -at the crime scene?

94
00:06:47,681 --> 00:06:51,881
Our travel tumblers were identical.

95
00:06:51,881 --> 00:06:54,581
I've accidentally touched it before.

96
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,881
It must've happened then.

97
00:06:56,881 --> 00:06:59,081
Accidentally, you say?

98
00:06:59,081 --> 00:07:02,181
We'll be confirming that.

99
00:07:04,481 --> 00:07:06,581
"Mouri Detective Agency" -Hey, kid.

100
00:07:06,581 --> 00:07:11,181
You're sure Mr. Hashizume took the wrong travel tumbler, right?

101
00:07:11,181 --> 00:07:13,381
Yeah, but...

102
00:07:13,381 --> 00:07:15,381
What is it, Conan?

103
00:07:15,381 --> 00:07:18,181
It may have been my imagination,

104
00:07:18,181 --> 00:07:20,481
but it seemed like Mr. Hashizume

105
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:25,281
deliberately took Mr. Kagazume's travel tumbler.

106
00:07:25,281 --> 00:07:26,281
-What? -What?

107
00:07:26,281 --> 00:07:28,181
Is that true?

108
00:07:28,181 --> 00:07:34,281
Then if he deliberately left his own poisoned tumbler

109
00:07:34,281 --> 00:07:37,581
and Mr. Kagazume drank from it without knowing...

110
00:07:37,581 --> 00:07:40,281
Yeah, it's murder.

111
00:07:40,281 --> 00:07:42,181
But later...

112
00:07:42,181 --> 00:07:46,081
Mr. Kagazume listened to what I said.

113
00:07:46,081 --> 00:07:49,181
He knew it wasn't his.

114
00:07:49,181 --> 00:07:50,581
But...

115
00:07:50,581 --> 00:07:52,581
You're right. That is weird.

116
00:07:52,581 --> 00:07:56,181
We can ask Mr. Hashizume about it.

117
00:07:56,181 --> 00:07:58,181
Well, actually...

118
00:08:00,081 --> 00:08:02,281
What? You have an alibi?

119
00:08:02,281 --> 00:08:07,881
Yeah. It was yesterday night from 7 pm to 9 pm, right?

120
00:08:07,881 --> 00:08:09,781
I was...

121
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:15,281
He was staking out a celebrity's affair.

122
00:08:15,281 --> 00:08:16,881
Is there proof?

123
00:08:16,881 --> 00:08:18,281
Yes.

124
00:08:18,281 --> 00:08:23,481
"Cheetah Delivery" -He remembered the company name

125
00:08:23,481 --> 00:08:28,281
and appearance of the deliveryman who arrived during that time.

126
00:08:29,381 --> 00:08:32,981
We confirmed his story with the delivery company.

127
00:08:32,981 --> 00:08:36,781
It would've been impossible for Mr. Hashizume to be at the crime scene.

128
00:08:36,781 --> 00:08:39,981
Mouri, delivery.

129
00:08:39,981 --> 00:08:41,081
Coming.

130
00:08:41,081 --> 00:08:43,881
"Cheetah Delivery" -Hello. I have a package for you.

131
00:08:43,881 --> 00:08:45,781
I'm here at the time you specified.

132
00:08:45,781 --> 00:08:47,481
Okay.

133
00:08:47,481 --> 00:08:48,981
Could it be...

134
00:08:50,081 --> 00:08:54,181
This is it. Mr. Hashizume claims he was here,

135
00:08:54,181 --> 00:08:59,181
watching that apartment building from 6 pm to 7 am.

136
00:08:59,181 --> 00:09:03,081
Conan, did Mr. Mouri really ask you to investigate this place?

137
00:09:03,081 --> 00:09:05,481
Hey, look.

138
00:09:05,481 --> 00:09:07,381
What's this?

139
00:09:07,381 --> 00:09:10,681
This is probably from a camera tripod.

140
00:09:13,981 --> 00:09:15,381
Hello?

141
00:09:15,381 --> 00:09:18,681
Yes, thank you for taking my call earlier.

142
00:09:18,681 --> 00:09:20,281
What?

143
00:09:22,581 --> 00:09:25,281
So the old man was right.

144
00:09:25,281 --> 00:09:30,781
Yeah. The delivery Mr. Hashizume saw had a specified delivery time.

145
00:09:30,781 --> 00:09:32,581
Not only that, but the address was unknown,

146
00:09:32,581 --> 00:09:36,081
and the sender's name on the voucher was made up.

147
00:09:36,081 --> 00:09:38,781
Did Mr. Hashizume send it?

148
00:09:38,781 --> 00:09:46,481
Yeah. He filmed the delivery using an unmanned camera on a tripod.

149
00:09:46,481 --> 00:09:48,981
During that time, he went to the crime scene.

150
00:09:48,981 --> 00:09:52,781
Later he checked the video so he'd have an alibi.

151
00:09:55,381 --> 00:09:58,981
Which means it was premeditated murder.

152
00:09:58,981 --> 00:10:03,181
We found the evidence to support it in a surprising location.

153
00:10:04,681 --> 00:10:09,881
On the flash drive plugged into the victim's laptop.

154
00:10:11,081 --> 00:10:15,881
On it we found a plan to murder...

155
00:10:15,881 --> 00:10:17,181
"Murder Plan"

156
00:10:17,181 --> 00:10:18,481
"By Hiroshi Kagazume"

157
00:10:19,981 --> 00:10:22,581
you, Mr. Hashizume.

158
00:10:24,181 --> 00:10:26,981
The method and alibi trick in it

159
00:10:26,981 --> 00:10:29,681
is exactly as we just described.

160
00:10:29,681 --> 00:10:31,881
"Alibi fabrication" -According to the plan,

161
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:33,781
he meant to "switch out travel tumblers

162
00:10:33,781 --> 00:10:36,481
and return poisoned tumbler to Hashizume".

163
00:10:36,481 --> 00:10:38,581
"Exchange tumbler for my own".

164
00:10:38,581 --> 00:10:41,381
"Reconcile with a toast".

165
00:10:41,381 --> 00:10:43,181
"Send him to underworld".

166
00:10:44,981 --> 00:10:50,281
Later, "claim Hashizume was stressed about lack of progress at work,

167
00:10:50,281 --> 00:10:51,981
suggesting suicide,

168
00:10:51,981 --> 00:10:56,981
and write obituary about the loss of a rival and friend."

169
00:10:56,981 --> 00:11:01,281
He was quite the particular criminal.

170
00:11:01,281 --> 00:11:03,181
Or maybe it was conceit.

171
00:11:03,181 --> 00:11:04,981
Indeed.

172
00:11:04,981 --> 00:11:08,881
What is it? Something's not right.

173
00:11:08,881 --> 00:11:13,881
You either accidentally took or stole the victim's flash drive,

174
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:16,381
and read its contents.

175
00:11:16,381 --> 00:11:20,481
You learned of his plan to kill you and became enraged,

176
00:11:20,481 --> 00:11:23,181
and decided to murder him using the same method.

177
00:11:23,181 --> 00:11:25,481
No.

178
00:11:25,481 --> 00:11:30,481
You pretended to accidentally take the victim's travel tumbler home

179
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:32,781
and poisoned it.

180
00:11:32,781 --> 00:11:33,881
No!

181
00:11:33,881 --> 00:11:37,681
You invited the victim out so you could return it

182
00:11:37,681 --> 00:11:39,581
and exchanged tumblers with him.

183
00:11:39,581 --> 00:11:42,081
You made him think you reconciled and made him drink it.

184
00:11:42,081 --> 00:11:44,781
No...

185
00:11:49,481 --> 00:11:51,381
What?

186
00:11:51,381 --> 00:11:52,481
Huh?

187
00:12:02,948 --> 00:12:06,148
"Murder Plan By Akira Hashizume"

188
00:12:06,148 --> 00:12:08,648
What is this?

189
00:12:08,648 --> 00:12:10,848
Inspector!

190
00:12:10,848 --> 00:12:13,148
It's the murder plan we found

191
00:12:13,148 --> 00:12:18,748
on the flash drive we seized from Mr. Hashizume.

192
00:12:18,748 --> 00:12:22,548
His target is the victim, Mr. Kagazume.

193
00:12:22,548 --> 00:12:23,548
What?

194
00:12:23,548 --> 00:12:27,948
Both plans were written at nearly the same time.

195
00:12:27,948 --> 00:12:32,748
There are also no signs the documents were unlocked and read.

196
00:12:32,748 --> 00:12:34,548
Which means...

197
00:12:34,548 --> 00:12:39,648
Yeah. Unbelievably enough, they coincidentally created the same plan

198
00:12:39,648 --> 00:12:43,048
"Murder Plan By Akira Hashizume" -to murder the other.

199
00:12:44,548 --> 00:12:48,348
Because they're so alike, huh?

200
00:12:48,348 --> 00:12:50,448
But still...

201
00:12:52,348 --> 00:12:54,248
That's right.

202
00:12:54,248 --> 00:12:59,448
I tried to kill Kagazume according to the plan.

203
00:12:59,448 --> 00:13:03,348
I fabricated an alibi, poisoned the travel tumbler,

204
00:13:03,348 --> 00:13:05,848
invited Kagazume out and went to meet him.

205
00:13:05,848 --> 00:13:07,648
I'm sure of it.

206
00:13:07,648 --> 00:13:09,248
But...

207
00:13:09,248 --> 00:13:10,848
But when I went...

208
00:13:11,948 --> 00:13:14,948
Kagazume was already dead.

209
00:13:14,948 --> 00:13:15,948
-What? -What?

210
00:13:15,948 --> 00:13:18,148
He was dead when you got there?

211
00:13:18,148 --> 00:13:19,648
That's absurd.

212
00:13:19,648 --> 00:13:21,948
It's too convenient!

213
00:13:21,948 --> 00:13:23,548
You're right.

214
00:13:24,648 --> 00:13:27,248
But it's true.

215
00:13:27,248 --> 00:13:29,648
I ran,

216
00:13:29,648 --> 00:13:31,548
washed the tumbler,

217
00:13:31,548 --> 00:13:33,448
and threw it away.

218
00:13:33,448 --> 00:13:35,748
Quit playing dumb.

219
00:13:35,748 --> 00:13:39,148
Who else could have killed him?

220
00:13:40,648 --> 00:13:42,948
Those two...

221
00:13:42,948 --> 00:13:45,348
Mr. Mouri thinks they're suspicious?

222
00:13:45,348 --> 00:13:47,648
No.

223
00:13:47,648 --> 00:13:50,648
He just wants to know if they have alibis.

224
00:13:50,648 --> 00:13:55,548
We looked into it but it's unclear.

225
00:13:55,548 --> 00:13:58,748
Mr. Hosoda was out gathering information alone.

226
00:13:58,748 --> 00:14:01,548
Ms. Kuwana was working late in the office by herself.

227
00:14:01,548 --> 00:14:04,148
Neither had anyone to confirm their stories.

228
00:14:04,148 --> 00:14:06,748
Oh, really?

229
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:12,348
Pops asked me to do one other thing.

230
00:14:12,348 --> 00:14:13,448
Huh?

231
00:14:16,248 --> 00:14:18,848
Re-examine the crime scene?

232
00:14:18,848 --> 00:14:21,848
Is there something bothering Mr. Mouri?

233
00:14:21,848 --> 00:14:23,848
Can you show me the crime scene photos?

234
00:14:23,848 --> 00:14:24,848
Huh?

235
00:14:24,848 --> 00:14:26,648
Yeah, here.

236
00:14:28,648 --> 00:14:30,548
What's this?

237
00:14:30,548 --> 00:14:32,648
It's coffee.

238
00:14:32,648 --> 00:14:37,748
We think some coffee spilled from his tumbler when he collapsed.

239
00:14:37,748 --> 00:14:42,748
We found the same cyanide in it, so we're fairly certain.

240
00:14:42,748 --> 00:14:45,748
Then shouldn't it be on his pants, too?

241
00:14:45,748 --> 00:14:47,648
Based on the length of his pants,

242
00:14:47,648 --> 00:14:49,848
isn't it strange to only be on his socks?

243
00:14:49,848 --> 00:14:52,148
Now that you mention it,

244
00:14:52,148 --> 00:14:54,248
it certainly is odd.

245
00:14:54,248 --> 00:14:58,148
How did the victim, Mr. Kagazume, get here?

246
00:14:58,148 --> 00:15:00,148
By car.

247
00:15:00,148 --> 00:15:03,048
He parked on the embankment and walked here.

248
00:15:03,048 --> 00:15:05,048
Did you search the inside of the car?

249
00:15:05,048 --> 00:15:10,448
Yeah, but we didn't find anything suspicious.

250
00:15:10,448 --> 00:15:12,648
Search it again.

251
00:15:12,648 --> 00:15:14,948
Officer Chiba? This is Mouri.

252
00:15:14,948 --> 00:15:18,448
There's something I want you to look into.

253
00:15:21,448 --> 00:15:24,248
Is it true, Mouri?

254
00:15:24,248 --> 00:15:27,448
That you've uncovered the truth behind the case.

255
00:15:27,448 --> 00:15:32,248
What? I came here because you said you found new evidence to...

256
00:15:39,748 --> 00:15:43,848
Pops! Are you okay?

257
00:15:43,848 --> 00:15:47,048
Stand back, Conan.

258
00:15:47,048 --> 00:15:48,648
Okay!

259
00:15:50,048 --> 00:15:51,548
Excuse me.

260
00:15:51,548 --> 00:15:54,848
Allow me to explain the truth behind the case.

261
00:15:54,848 --> 00:16:00,248
First, Officer Takagi, what did you find in Mr. Kagazume's car?

262
00:16:01,448 --> 00:16:03,748
Right. On the floor of the driver's seat,

263
00:16:03,748 --> 00:16:07,148
we found traces of cyanide.

264
